gomodel:SYNGO_316  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this study, Zhao et al knocked down (KD) SCAMP5 in primary cultured neurons using shRNA. SypHy, a fusion protein of synaptophysin with pHluorin was used to measure the kinetics of exo- and endocytosis. Synaptic vesicle (SV) endocytosis during stimulation was severely defective in the SCAMP5 KD neurons and was fully rescued by the expression of HA-SCAMP5 resistant to shRNA (Fig. 6A-D).. Experimental description: Hippocampal neurons derived from embryonic day 18 Sprague Dawley fetal rats of either sex were prepared as described previously (Chang and De Camilli, 2001)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-22" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_316" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

